<collectingCountry box="[684,795,1577,1601]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="105" pageNumber="105">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[936,1012,1577,1601]" name="Bolivia" pageId="105" pageNumber="105">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and central 
<collectingCountry box="[1148,1212,1577,1601]" name="Brazil" pageId="105" pageNumber="105">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Arroyo-Cabrales, 2008a; Reid, 2009). The taxonomic status of this bat has been debated for most of the second half of the last century. Whereas some authors considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[1063,1183,1709,1733]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Mesophylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="105" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
